INSTALLATION
    UML2oWFN can be easily compiled and installed. See file "INSTALL" for
    instructions. Please also have a look at the file "REQUIREMENTS" for
    information on the tools required to run, compile, and develop UML2oWFN.


DOCUMENTATION
    The directory "doc" contains a documentation of UML2oWFN. It can also be
    downloaded at <http://service-technology.org/files/uml2owfn/uml2owfn.pdf>.


Contents of this Distribution
*****************************

Files
=====

`AUTHORS'
     A list of the authors of UML2oWFN, acknowledgements, and a contact
     address.

`ChangeLog'
     The change log listing all changes made during the distribution
     versions of UML2oWFN.

`COPYING'
     The GNU General Public License (GPL) under which UML2oWFN is
     distributed.

`INSTALL'
     Setup and Installation instructions and all information needed to
     bootstrap UML2oWFN.

`NEWS'
     News concerning the most recent version of UML2oWFN.

`README'
     This file.

Moreover, the distribution's root directory contains several files
controlling the setup, build and installation process. These files were
generated by the GNU Autotools.  For more information on the
installation process refer to the `INSTALL' file.

Directories
===========

`src'
     The sources of UML2oWFN.

     Each file contains a short documentation of what it does as well
     as Doxygen-styled comments (see
     `http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen' for details).(1)

`doc'
     The documentation of UML2oWFN consisting of a manual and an
     installation manual. The documentation is in Texinfo format and
     can be converted into many file formats using `make FORMAT' where
     `FORMAT' is a file format out of `dvi', `html', `pdf' or `ps'.

`tests'
     Several test processes to self-test UML2oWFN. 
     The tests can be triggered with `make check'.
     
`lola'
     Several LoLA configuration files that can be used to create the LoLA
     model checker variants for automated soundness analysis of translated
     processes.
